we can skip staging!
it's not normal, and we should not use it often!
we use stage to review the changes.

if we want to skip staging,
after modifying a file,
instead using "git add file_name" to move changes to stage,
we can use "git commit" directly!

git commit -a -m "skip staging!"

Note: when we skip staging, and using commit directly
      the git will update the stage area automatically!

Note: "-a" means
      commit all modified files.

Note: we can mix -a & -m together and write
      git commit -am "skip staging!"